                            <comment id="12991591" author="stack" created="Mon, 7 Feb 2011 20:49:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch is good.  +1 on commit.  FYI, there used to be a bit of a convention naming threads where thread would be prefixed by main thread name.  In this case it would be something like regionserver60020 (If you thread dump you see regionserver60020.compactor, regionserver60020.majorCompactionChecker&quot;, regionserver60020.leaseChecker&quot;, etc.).  You might want to keep up the tradition when you commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12991599" author="tlipcon" created="Mon, 7 Feb 2011 20:54:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hrm, I don&apos;t see a convenient way of getting the RS name from within LruBlockCache without breaking some of the layer encapsulation we&apos;ve got going on (a dependency backwards from HFile -&amp;gt; RS seems ugly)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How about commit as is and some day maybe we do an improvement? &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12991600" author="stack" created="Mon, 7 Feb 2011 20:56:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thats fine by me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
